課程概述 Course Description
       經營現代營建專案不僅僅是講究高度專業技術分工，更講求各項專業工程介面之整合。而後者往往就是成敗關鍵之所在；所需處理的介面從各種工項排程、預算、品質控制、到行政協調、法令規範、合約管理等等。如今專業工程師在處理各種工程介面問題時，如果能夠透過正確的談判觀念，加上熟練的協調技巧，不但可以降低不必要的誤解與衝突，更可以積極促進工程團隊之互信合作，提高工作績效。更何況工程進行當中所衍生之民眾抗爭，以及工程爭議調處，更有賴工程人員之談判能力。本課程針對工程專案所需，主旨於教導學生如何透過談判促進彼此信任，達成合作目的。有別於一般敵對雙方，互相猜忌所採行之詭詐伎倆之動機。課程主要目的在於幫助學生，明瞭談判過程並能有效管理：包含如何面對壓力下之創造談判價值、瞭解自己與他方需求、以及組織內外之協商等。內容包含講授御理談判(principled negotiation)之理論與方法，以及透過實際演練，幫助學生建構個人獨特之談判風格。 

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    Managing a modern construction project asks not only conglomerating many specialties to work but well integrating their interfaces while achieving the goal. Techniques for a successful integration job are thus crucial. A general integration job covers tasks scheduling, budgeting, quality controlling, daily administration, specifications and contracts managing…etc. Facing interface problems, a qualified engineer should be able to effectively mitigate troublesome misunderstandings and possible conflicts using healthy negotiation concepts as well as communication skills. A good collaboration climate for better performance should also be generated in the meantime. It has been long acknowledged in real practices that negotiation skill is an essential for a competent engineer to resolve commonly seen public confrontations and all kinds dispute nowadays. This course focuses on the need of collaboration for general engineering practices, while those tricky tactics employed in adversarial situations are then disregarded. The primary pedagogical goal is to help student to understand and manage effectively in the negotiation process regarding the tension between creating and distributing value, the tension between the need to empathize with other side’s interests, the need to assert one’s own interests, and the tension between internal and external negotiations.  Lectures embrace the principled negotiation theory with an emphasis on negotiation skill building. This course also helps students develop their negotiation styles via intensive exercises.    

